post_cb({"19267036": {"Id": "19267036", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Define that <code>static</code> member out of the class declaration:</p>\n<pre><code>class Commands {\nprotected:\n   static Container database; // &lt;-- It's just a declration\n};\n\nContainer Commands::database; // &lt;-- You should make a definition\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_19266935_19267036_0\">The declaration of a static data member in its class definition is not\n  a definition ... The definition for a static data member shall appear\n  in a namespace scope enclosing the member\u2019s class definition.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Your way to make it <code>protected</code> is OK to make it accessible for derived classes.</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "952747", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-09T08:58:07.490", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2013-10-09T08:42:45.087", "ParentId": "19266935", "CommentCount": "1", "LastEditDate": "2013-10-09T08:58:07.490", "OwnerUserId": "952747"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_19266935_19267247_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5903}, "so_19266935_19267036_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 0.9047619047619048, "section_id": 5907}}, "n3337": {"so_19266935_19267036_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 0.9047619047619048, "section_id": 5679}, "so_19266935_19267247_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5675}}, "n4659": {"so_19266935_19267036_0": {"length": 19, "quality": 0.9047619047619048, "section_id": 7389}, "so_19266935_19267247_0": {"length": 22, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 7385}}}, "19267247": {"Id": "19267247", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Your code looks ok except <em>missing definition of static Commands member database</em>.\nYou need to define <code>database</code> outside <code>commands</code> class</p>\n<pre><code>Container Commands::database;\n</code></pre>\n<p>\u00a7 <strong>9.4.2 Static members</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_19266935_19267247_0\"><strong>Static members obey the usual class member access rules (Clause 11)</strong>. When used in the declaration of a class member, the static specifier shall only be used in the member declarations that appear within the member-specification of the class definition.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>As <code>database</code> is a protected member of base class <code>Commands</code>, derived class <code>Add</code> should be able to access it by <code>::</code> operator or <code>.</code> operator from object.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-09T08:52:41.917", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2013-10-09T08:52:41.917", "ParentId": "19266935", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "951757"}, "19266935": {"ViewCount": "603", "Body": "<p>I have a question. If I have a static member in the superclass, how do I allow all sub-classes of this superclass access and use the static member.</p>\n<p>E.g.</p>\n<pre><code>/*Superclass*/\nclass Commands {\n   protected:\n            static Container database;\n};\n\n/*Sub class*/\nclass Add: public Commands {\n   public:\n            void add_floating_entry(std::string task_description);  \n};\n\n/*This gives me an error. add_floating_task is a method of the Container Class*/\nvoid Add::add_floating_entry(string task_description)\n{\n   database.add_floating_task(task_description);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>May I know what is wrong here? Thanks in advance!</p>\n<p>EDIT:</p>\n<p>The Container class is as follows</p>\n<pre><code>class Container {\nprivate:\n   vector&lt;Task_Info*&gt; calendar[13][32];\n   vector&lt;Task_Info*&gt; task_list;\npublic:\n   void add_floating_task(std::string task_description);\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>The error given is: \"Use of undeclared identifier \"database\"</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "19267036", "Title": "Accessing protected static members of Superclass by Sub-classes in C++", "CreationDate": "2013-10-09T08:37:51.150", "Id": "19266935", "CommentCount": "2", "LastEditDate": "2013-10-09T09:06:21.190", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2319536", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-09T09:25:41.470", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "2319536", "Tags": "<c++><inheritance><polymorphism><subclass><superclass>", "AnswerCount": "3"}, "19267987": {"Id": "19267987", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Since <code>static</code> member is shared between all objects.<code>Commands::database</code> should be OK.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-10-09T09:25:41.470", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-10-09T09:25:41.470", "ParentId": "19266935", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "1608646"}});